snippet.textDisplay: Hypocrite. Im sorry, but its the truth. We wanted every single manager post fergie out because of style of play. Now we have ole, he sold us a dream in style of play, got the job and went back to being defensive. And now we are going to be told to back the manager when ole is playing a style of play that is exactly what us fans have been moaning about for years. My standards wont be lowered, and that is why I want ole out and poch in.  Ole can go and prove himself with a lower team and lets see how that goes. He is learning on the job, we can see, the players keep saying he is learning everyday, we are man united. Not some league 2 club giving a shot to a manager like Sol Campbell and hoping for the best. There are levels to all this and for me, its as simple as, I dont like ole's style of play. Formation, tactics, in game management like subs,  Zonal Marking, everytime he opens his mouth in interviews he gets caught out with something. The signs are there.

With Jones, Pereira, lingard, smalling, Sanchez, pogba, rojo likely to leave, we can raise ample cash to get players that will bring the same positivity that Bruno has brought and not the ones concerned about their hairstyles or clothing line
When the transfer season starts, our first business must be getting rid of Jones.
